      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's great that you're being cautious, but Advil is not the best option for you with chronic kidney disease. I recommend you consult your doctor, but in the meantime, you can try taking an over-the-counter pain reliever like acetaminophen (Tylenol), which is generally safe for most people with kidney disease. However, be sure to follow the recommended dosage and don't exceed it, as excessive acetaminophen can still harm your kidneys.",
